# PeerPoint is a peer counselling platform for Strathmore University where trained student peer counsellors provide support to fellow students under administrative oversight.
## Context
PeerPoint is a peer counselling platform for Strathmore University. This is the frontend-only phase: mock auth, no backend calls, realistic placeholder data only. The goal is a clean, demoable UI ‚Äî not a finished product.

## Tech Stack
- Vite + React 18
- React Router v6
- Tailwind CSS
- React Context for state (no Redux/Zustand/other state libs)
- lucide-react for all icons (no inline SVGs unless lucide doesn't have the icon)
- One component per file

## Folder Structure
```
src/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/   (shared UI: Button, Card, Badge, Input, CrisisSupportCard, etc.)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ context/      (AuthContext.jsx)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ data/         (mock data files)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layouts/      (PublicLayout, DashboardLayout)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pages/        (actual screens ‚Äî Landing, Login, Signup, dashboards, etc.)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ routes/       (AppRouter.jsx, ProtectedRoute.jsx ‚Äî routing config only, no screens here)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ App.jsx
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.jsx
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ index.css
```

## Design Tokens (registered in tailwind.config.js theme.extend.colors)
- primary: #2D7D8A
- primary-dark: #006470
- background: #F8F6F2
- dark-surface: #1E2A35
- success: #10B981
- warning: #F59E0B
- danger: #EF4444
- crisis: #CC0000
- crisis-light: #FFDAD4

## CRITICAL COLOR RULE
`crisis` and `crisis-light` exist ONLY for the CrisisSupportCard component (the 24/7 emergency helpline card seen on student/counsellor dashboards). Never use `crisis` colors for buttons, nav items, badges, links, active states, or anything else anywhere in the app. If something needs urgent/error styling outside the crisis card, use `danger`, not `crisis`. This is a hard rule, not a style suggestion.

## Typography
- Headings: `font-heading` ‚Üí Plus Jakarta Sans
- Body: `font-body` ‚Üí Work Sans
- Both loaded via Google Fonts `<link>` tags in `index.html`, and mapped in `tailwind.config.js` under `theme.extend.fontFamily`.

## Visual Style
Calm, trustworthy, soft, student-friendly, modern. Generous spacing, rounded corners (`rounded-xl` / `rounded-2xl`), layered cards, soft shadows, subtle gradients where tasteful. Avoid sharp corners, dense enterprise-SaaS layouts, or default Bootstrap-looking components.

## Interactions (required on all interactive elements)
- Buttons: hover ‚Üí `scale(1.02)` + `translateY(-2px)`, smooth transition
- Cards: subtle lift/shadow increase on hover
- Inputs: animated focus state with a visible focus ring
- No static, lifeless interfaces

## Auth (mock only ‚Äî no API calls anywhere in this phase)

User shape:

```js
{
  id,
  fullName,
  email,
  role: "student" | "counsellor" | "admin",
  isVerified
}
```

### Account Lifecycle

All new users register as **students**.

There is no public counsellor signup flow.

There is no public admin signup flow.

A counsellor account is created when an administrator promotes an existing student account to the `counsellor` role.

An admin account can only exist as a predefined system account in this frontend demo.

### Signup Rules

Students may sign up using a Strathmore University email address.

Valid signup email format:

```text
@strathmore.edu
```

If the email does not end with `@strathmore.edu`, display the inline error:

```text
Please use your Strathmore University email address.
```

Display the error directly beneath the email field.

Do not silently fail validation.

New signups should create a mock user with:

```js
{
  role: "student",
  isVerified: true
}
```

### Test Logins

Student:

```text
student@strathmore.edu
123456
```

Redirect:

```text
/student
```

Counsellor:

```text
counsellor@strathmore.edu
123456
```

Redirect:

```text
/counsellor
```

Admin:

```text
admin@strathmore.edu
123456
```

Redirect:

```text
/admin
```

### Email Rules

PeerPoint is restricted to members of the Strathmore University community.

All accounts in the system must use:

```text
@strathmore.edu
```

This applies to:

* Students
* Peer Counsellors
* Administrators

Any other email domain should be rejected with an inline validation error.

Error message:

```text
Please use your Strathmore University email address.
```

These test accounts exist only for frontend routing and demonstration purposes.

They do not imply public signup paths for counsellors or administrators.

### Route Behaviour

Unauthenticated users:

```text
Landing
Login
Signup
```

Authenticated students:

```text
/student
```

Authenticated counsellors:

```text
/counsellor
```

Authenticated admins:

```text
/admin
```

Role-based routing should be enforced through the existing mock authentication flow.

Signup validation: email must end in `@strathmore.edu` for both student and counsellor signup. If not, show an inline error: "Please use your Strathmore University email address." Do not block on this silently ‚Äî show the message under the email field.

## Mock Data
Keep schemas generic and simple for now ‚Äî they are NOT meant to mirror the production database schema yet (that'll be aligned later once the backend is finalized). Just enough shape to make the dashboards look realistic: counsellor profiles (bio, specialties, availability), sessions, pending requests, recent activity, platform stats.

## Output Rules
No TODOs. No omitted files. No placeholder comments like `// add logic here`. Every file must be complete and runnable as written.
